13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1239 of Title 69, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. As used in this section, the term "invasive woody species"
18 means a tree or shrub species that is rapidly encroaching into
19 adjoining lands and is likely to cause harm to the environment or
20 economy. Invasive woody species include, but are not limited to,
21 Juniperus virginiana (Eastern Redcedar), Juniperus scopulorum (Rocky
22 Mountain juniper), Juniperus monosperma (oneseed juniper) and
23 Tamarix ramosissima (salt cedar).
