1 B. The Oklahoma Department of Transportation shall establish
2 and implement a program for the systematic identification, removal,
3 and management of invasive woody species within rights-of-way under
4 its jurisdiction. The eradication program shall include the
5 following components:
6 1. Surveys to identify the presence and extent of invasive
7 woody species;
8 2. Development of a prioritized plan for eradication and
9 control;
10 3. Use of best management practices for removal, including
11 methods that minimize harm to native vegetation and prevent soil
12 erosion;
13 4. Monitoring and follow-up measures to prevent
14 reestablishment; and
15 5. Collaboration with local, state, and federal agencies, as
16 well as nongovernmental organizations, to leverage expertise and
17 resources.
18 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
